																								Dhaka, Nov. 29 (Reuters): A Bangladesh court has convicted a fugitive former government minister of tax evasion and sentenced him to eight years in prison, a lawyer for the prosecution said. The anti-corruption court also ordered that assets belonging to Ziaul Huq Zia, former state minister for local government and rural development, be seized.
